  Core Concept

  Evolution is triggered by species-specific unlock conditions. When a condition is met, evolution starts immediately. The trainer can cancel the evolution, which re-locks it. The condition must be met again
  for evolution to re-trigger.

  Unlock Conditions

  Each Pokemon species defines its own evolution unlock conditions. Conditions can be combined with AND/OR logic.

  Condition types include (not exhaustive):
  - Item use — a specific item is used on the Pokemon (e.g., Fire Stone on Eevee)
  - Held item + battle outcome — Pokemon wins a battle while holding a specific item (e.g., Scyther holding Steel Coat)
  - Environmental — Pokemon spends time in a specific environment (e.g., Magneton in a high-magnetism area)
  - Level threshold — Pokemon reaches a specific level (e.g., Charmander at level 16)
  - Move known — Pokemon knows a specific move
  - Gender — Pokemon is a specific gender

  Cancellation and Re-locking

  - When evolution starts, the trainer may cancel it
  - Cancelling re-locks the evolution — it does not remain "available"
  - The provoking condition must occur again to re-trigger (use another stone, win another battle, etc.)

  Item Consumption

  Items that provoke evolution (stones, etc.) are only consumed if the evolution completes. If the trainer cancels, the item is not spent.
